post_text:
AQUAFINA - VANDUSEN BEVARAGES FALL SPORT PARENT MEETING @ Astoria High School

Van Dusen Beverages, locally owned and operated since 1849 (the oldest family business in the state of Oregon) has graciously donated AQUAFINA to AHS student-athletes for the 2018-19 school year. AQUAFINA & VAN DUSEN BEVERAGES will help kick start this sponsorship by providing beverages at the Astoria High School Fall Sport Parent Meeting on Thursday, August 9th. Doors will open at 6:30 P.M. in order to allow parents an opportunity to register their child and complete the paperwork process.

The Athletic Department program will begin at 7:00 P.M. in the Auditorium for all fall sport teams. At approximately 7:35 P.M. the head coaches of Boys and Girls Soccer, Football, Volleyball, Cheer, and Cross Country will conduct break out meetings. Parents of ALL Fall Sport Teams are encouraged to attend the 7:00 P.M. meeting in order to receive fall calendars and review school policies as well as to make certain their child is properly registered to begin official practices the week of August 13th.

Official practices for all Astoria High Fall Sport Teams will begin on Monday, August 13th. Please note the following location and start times for these practices:

Volleyball - Astoria High Main Gym - 9:00 A.M. Bring outdoor and indoor shoes.

Cross Country - Astoria High Track - 3:30 P.M.

Football - CMH FIELD - 8:00 A.M.

Boys Soccer - CMH FIELD - 7:00 P.M.

Girls Soccer - CMH FIELD - 7:00 P.M.

The 2018-19 Cheer Team will be conducting practice on Tuesday, August 14th at 9 A.M. in the mezzanine off the Astoria High Main Gymnasium.

CONGRATS!

post_text: All "IN SEASON" and "OUT OF SEASON" Astoria High student-athletes and Astoria Middle School 8th Graders are invited to participate in the winter core strength & conditioning program offered by the Astoria High coaching staff. "IN SEASON" (student-athletes participating in basketball, wrestling, and swimming) participants are encouraged to participate in two workouts per week. "OUT of SEASON" (student-athletes not currently participating in a winter sport but will participate in either a fall and/or spring sport) participants are encouraged to attend three workouts per week. Workouts are offered before school at 6:15 A.M. and after school at 3:45 P.M. every Monday, Wednesday, and Friday. The weight room is also open after school every Thursday at 2:15 P.M. Please contact the Athletic Department if you have any questions about the winter core strength and conditioning program.
